This poem is generally supposed to have been composed at the commencement of the Perusian war, A.U.C. 713—- the year following the battle of Philippi, when the state os Italy was indeed deplorable, and the fortunes of Horace himself at the worst. He had forfeited his patrimony, and it was two years before he was even introduced to Maecenas. At that time he would have been twenty-four. The poem
